what:
where:
Abu Dhabi
5 years' experience in chemical/mechanical engineering or production/process operations preferably with an oil producing company. Minimum experience in three of the sub-surface operations (Coiled tubing, Wireline , Well testing, Logging, Well integrity) Very good knowledge of English
Job Description:
Monitors, analyses and reports on the performance of all oil, gas, non-associated gas, production facilities in the assigned field, in terms of both equipment efficiency and process effectiveness, from wellheads through processing/treatment plants, to and including distribution pipelines. Investigates problems; initiates, develops and progresses improvements and modifications to existing facilities; evaluates alternatives for new facilities, specifying appropriate design criteria; and provides technical data and undertakes analyses on production operations as required. Maybe assigned as the technical specialist for one area of plant or facilities, but is expected to handle peak workload or leave relief assignments in other production areas, based on operational requirements. Directs and coordinates the activities of assigned personnel in Production Engineering Section. Performs supervisory functions and exercises financial authority at the level established by management for the position. Reviews, checks, analyses and manipulates process and equipment production data to monitor and maintain familiarity with all production activities and status, to identify existing or potential problems, to calculate mass balances of production for fiscal and reservoir management purposes, and to predict trends. Participates in the setting of production targets and performance standards and oversees the preparation of the Production Department's input into the Operations Manager Assigned field's monthly report. Investigates and troubleshoots any anomalies, irregularities or problems related to production facilities on any plant or process. Obtains and analyses relevant data on circumstances and situations and develops appropriate solutions or specifies requirements for additional information or specialist assistance.
Interested qualified candidates may revert along with their most updated resume.
